COPS are looking for this man. His name is Tomeya Mathebula and he’s 32 years old. The police are looking for him in connection with a murder that took place outside a tavern in Ivory Park, Ekurhuleni last July. The police started investigating the murder immediately after it happened and all leads point to Mathebula. He had by then left Ivory Park and has not been seen since. During an argument, the suspect allegedly stabbed a 30-year-old man to death. The dead man was from Hospital View in Tembisa. He was found with a stab wound to the chest. Anyone who knows Mathebula’s whereabouts is asked to contact Detective-Constable Edmond Lebopo on 079 031 2230.